    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Order containing 22 species in two families. Includes bandicoots and bilbies, all having a plump, arch-backed body with a long tapering snout, very large upright ears, relatively long, thin legs, a thin tail, fused second and third toes, and several pairs of lower front teeth.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
